title.narrative: UNICEF Operations in the field are well coordinated and supported; UNICEF achieves and maintains adequate levels of preparedness and responds effectively to humanitarian situations fulfilling its Core Commitments for Children in Humanitarian Situations.

description.narrative:
The field offices and UNICEF led clusters are fully functional to provide urgent and lifesaving humanitarian services to most vulnerable children and families across all 34 provinces in Afghanistan.
Effective emergency preparedness and response systems are in place. From 1 January to 30 June 2020, UNICEF has reached out to some 370,000 most vulnerable people including over 275,000 children with lifesaving integrated humanitarian assistances. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/07/2020
